(40, 1, '2016-10-02 11:41:17', '2016-10-02 11:41:17', 'Amanda Hope Rainbow Angel’s is a non-profit, support and educational organization designated by the IRS as a 501 (c) 3 tax-deductible, tax-exempt organization. This organization was founded in 2013 in celebration of Amanda Hope’s life that ended all too soon when she lost her battle against Leukemia. During her four year fight, Amanda Hope dreamed that one day she would design a fun clothing line for kids in the same type of situation that would provide comfort and dignity during treatment. Here is Amanda Hope’s dream!\r\n<h3>Our Mission:</h3>\r\nBring dignity and comfort into the harsh world of childhood cancer and other life-threatening diseases.\r\n<h3>Our Vision:</h3>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Provide Comfycozy’s Care™ gifts to all children diagnosed with cancer and other blood-related disorders.</li>\r\n 	<li>Support healthcare professionals in providing person-centered care to children and their families with empathy and understanding.</li>\r\n 	<li>Help families have voice and choice above harsh protocols often present in the healthcare system.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Problem – Children and Families in Crisis</h3>\r\nIn 2012, an estimated 16,000 new diagnoses of cancer are expected to occur among children 0 to 14 years of age. When a child is diagnosed with cancer or life-threatening illness, fear and shock ensues. Parents and family members are immediately faced with overwhelming decisions and issues regarding the care and well-being of their child. Often spanning months and years, the child’s treatment becomes the center of the family’s universe. The strength they will need for this battle is second only to the fear for their child’s life.\r\n\r\nThe physical, emotional, spiritual and financial toll that this horrible disease and other life-threatening illnesses have on children and their families is unimaginable – until you are there. Provided by an endless stream of healthcare professionals, the myriad of appointments, tests, procedures and potential surgeries endured by the child and family only contributes to the family’s loss of voice, dignity, modesty and control.\r\n<h3>Solution – Amanda Hope Rainbow Angel’s</h3>\r\nAmanda Hope Rainbow Angel’s will provide support to children and their families dealing with cancer and other life-threatening diseases through the following three programs. The geographic scope has begun in Arizona at Phoenix Children’s Hospital. Contingent on funding and philanthropy, Amanda Hope Rainbow Angel’s will expand to other major pediatric hospitals throughout the nation such as St. Jude Children’s Research Hospital, Seattle Children’s Hospital and Children’s National Medical Center.\r\n<h4>I. Comfycozy’s Care™ Gifts</h4>\r\n<strong>Who?</strong> All children diagnosed with cancer or blood-related illness will receive a Comfycozy’s Care Gift.\r\n\r\n<strong>What?</strong> Comfycozy’s Care™ Gifts are bright, washable backpacks that contain Comfycozy’s T-Shirts that are specially designed with zippers, pockets and holes allowing healthcare professionals access to a child’s ports and tubes while the child’s body remains covered. Providing dignity for the Journey. These T-shirts are in fun tie-dye colors, come in every size imaginable and the kids, families and healthcare professionals love them already!\r\n\r\nThis gift package also includes educational material for the family, supportive material about community resources and other “fun stuff” just for the child.\r\n\r\n<strong>When?</strong> Now! In December 2012, all children diagnosed with cancer or blood-related illness receiving out-patient and in-patient services at Phoenix Children’s Hospital received a Comfycozy’s Care™ gift package. All children receiving these same services at Cardon Children’s Hospital in Scottsdale will receive Comfycozy’s Care™ gift packages in February, 2013.\r\n<h4>II. Supporting Health Care Professionals</h4>\r\n<strong>Who?</strong> The care and treatment provided by health care professionals (i.e., physicians, nurses, technicians and office and hospital personnel, etc.) has a tremendous impact on the health and well-being of the child and their family. While the treatment protocols these professionals follow are of the utmost importance, it is also imperative that empathy and dignity be a priority at all times in all environments.\r\n\r\n<strong>What?</strong> Amanda Hope Rainbow Angel’s will develop and distribute educational material focused on helping medical professionals understand person-centered care, the strengths of the child and family, and the fear the family is experiencing. Workshops and presentations will be conducted at health care professional conferences, trade shows and meetings to discuss the importance of supporting family voice and dignity through empathy and understanding.\r\n\r\n<strong>When?</strong> In 2013, our volunteer ‘Angels’ will interact directly with families, health care professionals and hospital and clinic personnel while distributing Comfycozy’s Care™ Gifts to 1) provide written and verbal information, 2) identify opportunities for developing and providing additional materials and information and 3) identify health care professionals who practice this model and can support others.\r\n<h4>III. Helping Families Have Voice and Choice</h4>\r\n<strong>Who?</strong> It is vital for families to understand that they are their child’s advocate –no-one else can take their place in this role. Families must have voice and choice in their child’s healthcare decisions and not be afraid to challenge healthcare protocols, professionals and insurance companies.\r\n\r\n<strong>What?</strong> Amanda Hope Rainbow Angel’s will provide advocacy support through community resources, a hotline, volunteer advocates and other supports. We will also provide financial assistance to families in need such as utility payments, childcare, etc.\r\n\r\n<strong>Win Win.</strong> All Comfycozy’s for chemo are made by 2 organizations: “Dresses for Orphans” who make clothes for orphans in 22 countries around the world and “Poonman Designs” who’s mission is to rescue young women from domestic violence and the sex trade Industry in India. Giving the dignity and training to make a better life for them and there children.\r\n\r\n<strong>When?</strong> As soon as we receive your help and support.', '<h1 style="color: white; font-weight: bold; text-align:center; font-size:40px; padding: 25px;">About</h1>', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'about', '', '', '2016-10-02 17:35:36', '2016-10-02 17:35:36', '', 0, 'http://localhost/?page_id=40', 0, 'page', '', 0),
