(114, 1, '2016-10-02 16:35:11', '2016-10-02 16:35:11', '<h3>MEET THE BOARD</h3>\r\n<h3><img class="alignnone size-medium" src="http://www.amandahoperainbowangels.org/media/theboard.jpg" alt="" width="966" height="550" /></h3>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h3><img class="alignnone size-medium" src="http://www.amandahoperainbowangels.org/media/lorraine.png" alt="" width="270" height="270" /></h3>\r\n<h3>Lorraine Tallman</h3>\r\n<h4>Founder and Executive Director</h4>\r\nLorraine is the driving force behind Amanda Hope Rainbow Angel’s and Comfycozy’s for Chemo. Her personal experience in the pediatric cancer treatment world, sparked her lifelong devotion to advocacy and support for children with cancer and their families. She is committed to fulfilling Amanda’s last wish to provide dignity and empowerment to every Oncology and Hematology patient through the gift of their very own Comfycozy.\r\n\r\nShe is a member of the Steering Committee for the Arizona Childhood Cancer Coalition. She serves on the Family Advisory Council and the Memorial Service Grievance Committee at Phoenix Children’s Hospital. She also teaches the ‘Family Centered Care’ class to their new healthcare professionals.\r\n\r\nShe is a sought after speaker for Mother’s Grace, MASK magazine, the Child Life Specialist Association, and many other organizations.\r\n\r\nCurrently, she is collaborating with C.R. Bard, an international medical device company, on the development of a medical port needle device for easy one-time access. By limiting the number of pokes the patient’s anxiety and discomfort are reduced.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium" src="http://www.amandahoperainbowangels.org/media/herman.png" alt="" width="300" height="300" />\r\n<h3>Herman Lewkowitz</h3>\r\n<h4>President</h4>\r\nHerman is a Senior Private Banker for CoBiz Private Bank’s Arizona market. He is a member of the Board of Directors of the First Tee of Phoenix, as well as a member of the board and on the Investment Committee for the Crisis Nursery Foundation and a Life Member of the Thunderbirds. Herman is married with three kids and is devoted to helping pediatric cancer patients via the Amanda Hope Rainbow Angel’s foundation.\r\n\r\nHe earned a BSBA from the University of Arizona double majoring in Finance &amp; Real Estate; and an MBA from Arizona State University.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium" src="http://www.amandahoperainbowangels.org/media/kathryn.png" alt="" width="272" height="272" />\r\n<h3>Kathryn Marchwick</h3>\r\n<h4>Secretary</h4>\r\nKathryn is a CFP and Investment Advisory Representative in the Greater Phoenix Metropolitan area with over 30 years of investment and financial planning experience. She is currently affiliated with Williams Financial Broker Dealer as an Independent Representative and Financial Planner. She serves as a member of the Financial Planning Council at Blessed Sacrament in Scottsdale, Arizona.\r\n\r\nKathryn earned an Associates Degree from the Kenosha Memorial Hospital School of Histotechnology and attended the University of Wisconsin Parkside.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium" src="http://www.amandahoperainbowangels.org/media/marty.png" alt="" width="270" height="270" />\r\n<h3>Marty Tallman</h3>\r\n<h4>Founder, Treasurer, Planned Giving and Endowment Committee Chair</h4>\r\n“The Original Comfycozy” First and Foremost, Amanda’s loving Dad (Non-Biological) and Lorraine’s adoring Husband! Way too early in our life together, our sole focus became the healing of Amanda and as importantly assuring Amanda’s comfort and dignity throughout her Battle with Acute Lymphoblastic Leukemia. We Founded ComFycozy’s to full fill Amanda’s Dream to give every child a comfortable shirt that allowed them to receive their Chemo treatments without undressing.\r\n\r\nWe founded Amanda Hope Rainbow Angels to expand our family assistance and the Gift of “Comfycozy’s” to every child!\r\n\r\nMarty Graduated from the University of San Diego, with a BA Degree in accounting and a Minor in Leadership. He has founded import/export, Real Estate and Mortgage Broker companies.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium" src="http://www.amandahoperainbowangels.org/media/tom.png" alt="" width="234" height="234" />\r\n<h3>Tom Garrity</h3>\r\n<h4>Public Relations Committee Chair</h4>\r\nTom is currently the CEO and President of the Stampede, Sioux Falls Sports, LLC and Quan Sports Marketing, LLC. Previously he was the SVP of Sales for the Houston Astros, the President of the Houston Aeros and Team President of the Cincinnati Mighty Ducks. He has also been affiliated with the Canaries baseball team, the Capitols hockey team and the Minnesota Wild hockey team.\r\n\r\nTom was recently named United States Hockey League executive of the year 2014-2015.\r\n\r\nTom provides a direction connection for us to numerous teams in the sports industry resulting in team and player support.\r\n\r\nHe earned his degree from the University of Wisconsin at Platteville.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium" src="http://www.amandahoperainbowangels.org/media/susan.png" alt="" width="221" height="221" />\r\n<h3>Susan Reina</h3>\r\n<h4>Family-Centered Care Committee Chair</h4>\r\nSusan is a Physician Assistant at Nextcare Urgent Care in Flagstaff and Phoenix. Working in research for the National Institutes of Health fostered her dedication to the healthcare industry. As committee chair, Susan provides leadership for the development and implementation of our “Person Centered Care” curriculum, designed for the Healthcare Providers specializing in pediatric cancer.\r\n\r\nSusan earned her undergrad degree from Northern Arizona University and her masters in physician assistant studies from AT Still University.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class="alignnone size-medium" src="http://www.amandahoperainbowangels.org/media/garth.png" alt="" width="217" height="216" />\r\n<h3>Garth Price</h3>\r\n<h4>Board Member</h4>\r\nGarth is currently the Chief Executive Officer of Sunstate Equipment, Co., and a former Certified Public Accountant and Manager with Deloitte &amp; Touche. Throughout his life Mr. Price has been active in his community where he has served in various capacities including the Executive Council of the Boys and Girls Clubs, the Audit Committee of a community bank, a member of the Executive Leadership Team of the Arizona American Heart Association, and an owner of Flip Dunk Sports, LLC, a trampoline and gymnastics center. As a member of the board, Garth provides leadership and experience that will help Amanda Hope Rainbow Angel’s develop further as a non-profit organization.\r\n\r\nGarth received his Bachelor of Science in Accountancy from Northern Arizona University.', '<h1 style="color: white; font-weight: bold; text-align:center; font-size: 50px; padding: 50px; @media screen and (max-width: 480px) { body { font-size: 30px; } }">Organization</h1>', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '66-revision-v1', '', '', '2016-10-02 16:35:11', '2016-10-02 16:35:11', '', 66, 'http://localhost/2016/10/02/66-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0);
